### CSS Variables (Custom Properties)

**CSS Variables** store reusable values through your stylesheet.

---

### Defining Variables

```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #3498db;
  --text-size: 16px;
  --spacing: 20px;
}
```

Use `--` prefix followed by the variable name.

---

### Using Variables

```css
.element {
  color: var(--primary-color);
  font-size: var(--text-size);
  padding: var(--spacing);
}
```

---

### Fallback Values

```css
.element {
  color: var(--primary-color, blue);
  /* Uses --primary-color if defined, otherwise 'blue' */
}
```

---

### Scope

Variables respect the cascade. Define globally in `:root` or locally in any selector.

```css
/* Global */
:root {
  --color: blue;
}

/* Local to .card */
.card {
  --color: red;
}

/* Local to .dark-section */
.dark-section {
  --bg: #333;
  --text: #fff;
}
```

---

### Changing Variables with Media Queries

```css
:root {
  --gap: 10px;
  --columns: 1fr;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  :root {
    --gap: 20px;
    --columns: 1fr 1fr;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  :root {
    --columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  }
}

.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: var(--columns);
  gap: var(--gap);
}
```

---

### Theming with Variables

```css
:root {
  --bg: white;
  --text: black;
  --primary: blue;
}

[data-theme="dark"] {
  --bg: #1a1a1a;
  --text: #f0f0f0;
  --primary: #66b3ff;
}

body {
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--text);
}
```

---

### Variables in calc()

```css
:root {
  --base-size: 16px;
}

.element {
  font-size: calc(var(--base-size) * 1.5);
  padding: calc(var(--spacing, 20px) * 2);
}
```

---

### Inspecting Variables

- Chrome DevTools -> Styles panel -> `:root` section
- Shows all defined CSS variables and their values
- You can edit them live

> **Best Practice:** Use CSS variables for colors, spacing, fonts, and breakpoints. They make theme changes and maintenance much easier.
